T1  - Trade in nominal assets: Monetary policy, and price level and exchange rate risk
AU  - Svensson, Lars E.O.
JO  - Journal of International Economics
VL  - 26
IS  - 1
SP  - 1
EP  - 28
PY  - 1989
DA  - 1989/02/01/
SN  - 0022-1996
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0022-1996(89)90036-6
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199689900366
AB  - The pattern of trade in nominal assets is predicted, using the Law of Comparative Advantage and autarky asset price differences. It is examined how different combinations of monetary policies and exchange rate regimes affect nominal assets' real return risk characteristics, their autarky prices, and hence their trade pattern, when countries differ with respect to their outputs or their attitudes toward risk. With incomplete world asset markets, different monetary policies and exchange rate regimes have dramatic effects on risk characteristics, nominal assets, and their trade pattern, as well as on aggregate capital and current accounts.
