UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199689900408
AB  - When a manufacturer cannot completely control the behavior of its retailers, raising tariffs may increase domestic welfare, benefit consumers, and harm domestic manufacturers. These results are illustrated in a model in which the manufacturer transfers monopoly power to retailers by limiting their number, so as to induce retailers to provide services to consumers. Conditions are derived for each group to benefit from higher tariffs.
